Manual Installation
If Winget is not available:

Download PHP for Windows at https://windows.php.net/download/

Choose the Thread Safe x64 ZIP version.

Extract the zip file to a folder, e.g., C:\php.

Add C:\php to your system PATH:

Open Edit the system environment variables > Environment Variables.

Under System variables, find Path, click Edit, then New, and add C:\php.

Click OK to save.

Open a new Command Prompt and verify PHP is available:

text
php -v
Running the PHP Application Locally
Navigate to your project folder:

text
cd C:\php_app_lab2
Run the built-in PHP web server:

text
php -S localhost:8080
Open browser and go to http://localhost:8080
